oc:kn_0a0487be a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing agent example blocks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never omit context or commentary from example blocks. Generic examples like 'user needs help' or examples without context fail to provide triggering signal." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing context means Claude cannot pattern-match the situation; missing commentary means Claude doesn't understand WHY to trigger" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_505827f6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When debugging agent triggering problems" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If an agent doesn't trigger, check: examples lack relevant keywords, context doesn't match usage, commentary is unclear, or assistant doesn't show Agent tool use. If it triggers too often, examples are too broad or overlap with other agents." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Triggering issues always trace back to example quality — specificity, coverage, and clarity of the triggering logic" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6211b17b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing multiple example blocks for the same agent" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Vary user message phrasing across examples to cover different ways users express the same intent (e.g., 'review my code', 'check this implementation', 'look over my changes')." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users phrase requests differently; covering multiple phrasings increases the probability that one will match the actual user message" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_8353ef6f a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any agent example block" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each example block must include Context, user message, assistant pre-response, commentary explaining WHY the agent triggers, and assistant triggering response. Omitting any element reduces triggering reliability." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Complete example structure gives Claude sufficient pattern-matching signal to trigger agents correctly across diverse user interactions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ad34a277 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining how many example blocks to write for an agent" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write 3-4 examples covering: (1) explicit request, (2) implicit request, (3) proactive trigger after relevant work, (4) edge case. Minimum 2, maximum 6." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Too few examples limits triggering coverage; too many bloats the description and dilutes signal" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_af234735 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing example blocks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never show the agent's output in examples — only show the triggering invocation (assistant: 'I'll use the [agent-name] agent to...')." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Examples should demonstrate WHEN and HOW to trigger the agent, not what the agent does after being triggered" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c0597189 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Standard template for all agent triggering examples" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """<example>
Context: [situation description]
user: "[exact user message]"
assistant: "[Claude's acknowledgment]"
<commentary>
[Why this agent triggers in this scenario]
</commentary>
assistant: "I'll use the [agent-name] agent to [what it will do]."
</example>""" .

oc:kn_f6dfac3c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating example blocks for a new or existing agent" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify the 4 triggering types for your agent (explicit, proactive, implicit, tool-usage pattern). 2. Write 3-4 examples covering these types with varied phrasings. 3. Include context, user message, pre-response, commentary, and trigger response in each. 4. Verify examples don't overlap with other agents' triggering conditions." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

